Items.Name: Members
Documentation: The current membership, stored as an ordered Vec.

Items.Name: Prime
Documentation: The current prime member, if one exists.

Calls.Name: add_member
Documentation: Add a member `who` to the set.
May only be called from `T::AddOrigin`.

Calls.Name: remove_member
Documentation: Remove a member `who` from the set.
May only be called from `T::RemoveOrigin`.

Calls.Name: swap_member
Documentation: Swap out one member `remove` for another `add`.
May only be called from `T::SwapOrigin`.
Prime membership is *not* passed from `remove` to `add`, if extant.

Calls.Name: reset_members
Documentation: Change the membership to a new set, disregarding the existing membership. Be nice and
pass `members` pre-sorted.
May only be called from `T::ResetOrigin`.

Calls.Name: change_key
Documentation: Swap out the sending member for some other key `new`.
May only be called from `Signed` origin of a current member.
Prime membership is passed from the origin account to `new`, if extant.

Calls.Name: set_prime
Documentation: Set the prime member. Must be a current member.
May only be called from `T::PrimeOrigin`.

Calls.Name: clear_prime
Documentation: Remove the prime member if it exists.
May only be called from `T::PrimeOrigin`.

Events.Name: MemberAdded
Documentation: The given member was added; see the transaction for who.

Events.Name: MemberRemoved
Documentation: The given member was removed; see the transaction for who.

Events.Name: MembersSwapped
Documentation: Two members were swapped; see the transaction for who.

Events.Name: MembersReset
Documentation: The membership was reset; see the transaction for who the new set is.

Events.Name: KeyChanged
Documentation: One of the members' keys changed.

Events.Name: Dummy
Documentation: Phantom member, never used.

Errors.Name: AlreadyMember
Documentation: Already a member.

Errors.Name: NotMember
Documentation: Not a member.
